Recommends: nginx, openssh-server
Description: Autonomous Intrusion Prevention System
 WardenIPS is a Linux-native, asynchronous intrusion prevention platform 
 that watches real service logs, scores suspicious behavior, and blocks 
 attackers at the firewall layer before they become a bigger problem.
 .
 Key features:
  * Real-time prevention with ipset/iptables enforcement
  * Built-in blocklist protection (AbuseIPDB curated lists)
  * ASN-based threat detection with weekly GeoLite2 updates
  * Live operational dashboard
  * Plugin-based detection (SSH, Minecraft, Nginx)
  * Systemd service integration
  * Professional CLI wrapper with colored output